# Hardware Requirements Specification

## Overview

The hardware system shall monitor a lithium ion battery pack and communicate battery data to a computer or wireless device.

## Definitions

BMS: Battery Management System  
ESP32: Microcontroller used for processing and communication  
SOC: State of Charge  
IC: Integrated Circuit  

## Functionality

HRS 01 - The device shall use an ESP32 microcontroller for processing and communication.

HRS 02 - The device shall use a BMS monitoring IC to measure battery cell voltages, current, and temperature.

HRS 03 - The device shall support lithium-ion battery packs.

HRS 04 - The device shall measure individual cell voltages.

HRS 05 - The device shall measure pack current.

HRS 06 - The device shall measure battery temperature using thermistors.

HRS 07 - The device shall provide USB serial communication to a computer.

HRS 08 - The device should support wireless communication using Bluetooth or Wi-Fi.

HRS 09 - The device shall include protection monitoring for overvoltage, undervoltage, overcurrent, and temperature faults.

HRS 10 - The device shall be powered from the battery pack.
